I can see some of your guy's point.  I worked my can off to get my SoW potions trivial and i still fail a ton.  The highest lvl shaman in the guild told me that he kept failing even up to 80 skill in alchemy.  Then i hear that only 3 or so types are even asked for.  Very depressing.  Also, i hate it when jerks undercut you.  I was in FV and just lost a ton of money getting trivial.  So to help recoup a bit of the tremendous cost i asked a high lvl shammie what the fair ranges are.  He said 100-120 plat and so i asked for 120 plat.  I mean its high end of fair, but its still fair.  Soon as i auctioned it this jerk goes off on me on how im ripping everyone off.  I even explained why i was charging a *bit* more than standard.  <P>He wouldnt listen.  Needless to say i lost alot of customers.  I made the point that some druids/wizzies port for 15 plat and some for 25 but no one screams about that, and he said to "stop turning this around on him".  He kept telling the zone to not buy from me that he seen someone 2 zones away selling them for 90 plat a stack.  Undercut me bad.  So not only does verant screw us, but other players too.  The most demand i do have for them is from my guild and i cant bring myself to sell them for more than cost.  Sometimes i get lucky and run into someone who buys 2-3.  Theres still a market for them, but you have to travel alot and have alot of patience.<P>Im still angry for verant making you be 58 to make a gate potion.  Theyre always ready to protect the porter's monopoly on travel, but give out sow or sow like effects to anyone who can plop down 5k.  Great.  Now verant can we buy porting rings for 5k each?  Then we would see the druids and wizards go up in arms.  What about Clarity earrings for 5k?  Or how about a dual weild bracer?  Were the only class whos abilities seem to get handed out alot.  Maybe im wrong<P>--------------------<P>"We all go a little mad sometimes"<BR>       -Norman Bates<BR>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
